thread.title: U.S. Government Bonds Edge Lower

author: Gunjan Banerji
title: U.S. Government Bonds Edge Lower
text:
U.S. government bond prices slipped Friday, pushing the yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note to its highest close since 2014.
The 10-year yield rose to 2.949%--the highest settle since January 2014â€”from 2.914% on Thursday. Yields rise as bond prices fall.
